Hamilton原理

$$\int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {\left( {\delta {W_{nc}} + \delta T - \delta V} \right){\rm{d}}t} = 0$$


势能

$$T = \int_0^L \frac{1}{2} m(x) \left( \frac{\partial u}{\partial t} \right)^2 \, dx$$

动能

$$V = \left. \frac{1}{2} k u^2 \right|_{x = 0} + \int_0^L \frac{1}{2} EA(x) \left( \frac{\partial u}{\partial x} \right)^2 \, dx$$

代入

$$
\begin{align*}
\int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {\left( {\delta {W_{nc}} + \delta T - \delta V} \right){\rm{d}}t} &amp;=
\int_{t_1}^{t_2} \left( \int_0^L f \delta u \, dx + \delta \int_0^L \frac{1}{2} m(x) \left( \frac{\partial u}{\partial t} \right)^2 \, dx - \delta \left( \left. \frac{1}{2} k u^2 \right|_{x = 0} + \int_0^L \frac{1}{2} EA(x) \left( \frac{\partial u}{\partial x} \right)^2 \, dx \right) \right) \, dt \\
&amp;= \int_{t_1}^{t_2} \left( \int_0^L f \delta u \, dx + \int_0^L m(x) \frac{\partial u}{\partial t} \delta \left( \frac{\partial u}{\partial t} \right) \, dx - \left. ku \delta u \right|_{x = 0} - \int_0^L EA(x) \frac{\partial u}{\partial x} \delta \left( \frac{\partial u}{\partial x} \right) \, dx \right) \, dt \\
&amp;= \int_{t_1}^{t_2} \left( \int_0^L f \delta u \, dx - \left. ku \delta u \right|_{x = 0} \right) \, dt + \int_0^L \int_{t_1}^{t_2} m(x) \frac{\partial u}{\partial t} \delta \left( \frac{\partial u}{\partial t} \right) \, dt \, dx - \int_{t_1}^{t_2} \int_0^L EA(x) \frac{\partial u}{\partial x} \delta \left( \frac{\partial u}{\partial x} \right) \, dx \, dt \\
&amp;= \int_{t_1}^{t_2} \left( \int_0^L \left( f - m(x) \frac{\partial^2 u}{\partial t^2} + \frac{\partial}{\partial x} \left( EA(x) \frac{\partial u}{\partial x} \right) \right) \delta u \, dx - \left. ku \delta u \right|_{x = 0} + \left. EA(x) \frac{\partial u}{\partial x} \delta u \right|_0^L \right) \, dt
\end{align*}
$$

所以方程为

$$m\left( x \right)\frac{{{\partial ^2}u}}{{\partial {t^2}}} - \frac{\partial }{{\partial x}}\left( {EA\left( x \right)\frac{{\partial u}}{{\partial x}}} \right) = f\left( {x,t} \right)$$

边界条件

$${\left. {\left( {EA\left( x \right)\frac{{\partial u}}{{\partial x}} + ku} \right)} \right|_{x = 0}} = 0,\;\;{\left. {EA\left( x \right)\frac{{\partial u}}{{\partial x}}} \right|_{x = L}} = ## 2.1

Hamilton原理

$$\int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {\left( {\delta {W_{nc}} + \delta T - \delta V} \right){\rm{d}}t} = 0$$


势能

$$T = \int_0^L \frac{1}{2} m(x) \left( \frac{\partial u}{\partial t} \right)^2 \, dx$$

动能

$$V = \left. \frac{1}{2} k u^2 \right|_{x = 0} + \int_0^L \frac{1}{2} EA(x) \left( \frac{\partial u}{\partial x} \right)^2 \, dx$$

代入

$$
\begin{align*}
\int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {\left( {\delta {W_{nc}} + \delta T - \delta V} \right){\rm{d}}t} &=
\int_{t_1}^{t_2} \left( \int_0^L f \delta u \, dx + \delta \int_0^L \frac{1}{2} m(x) \left( \frac{\partial u}{\partial t} \right)^2 \, dx - \delta \left( \left. \frac{1}{2} k u^2 \right|_{x = 0} + \int_0^L \frac{1}{2} EA(x) \left( \frac{\partial u}{\partial x} \right)^2 \, dx \right) \right) \, dt \\
&= \int_{t_1}^{t_2} \left( \int_0^L f \delta u \, dx + \int_0^L m(x) \frac{\partial u}{\partial t} \delta \left( \frac{\partial u}{\partial t} \right) \, dx - \left. ku \delta u \right|_{x = 0} - \int_0^L EA(x) \frac{\partial u}{\partial x} \delta \left( \frac{\partial u}{\partial x} \right) \, dx \right) \, dt \\
&= \int_{t_1}^{t_2} \left( \int_0^L f \delta u \, dx - \left. ku \delta u \right|_{x = 0} \right) \, dt + \int_0^L \int_{t_1}^{t_2} m(x) \frac{\partial u}{\partial t} \delta \left( \frac{\partial u}{\partial t} \right) \, dt \, dx - \int_{t_1}^{t_2} \int_0^L EA(x) \frac{\partial u}{\partial x} \delta \left( \frac{\partial u}{\partial x} \right) \, dx \, dt \\
&= \int_{t_1}^{t_2} \left( \int_0^L \left( f - m(x) \frac{\partial^2 u}{\partial t^2} + \frac{\partial}{\partial x} \left( EA(x) \frac{\partial u}{\partial x} \right) \right) \delta u \, dx - \left. ku \delta u \right|_{x = 0} + \left. EA(x) \frac{\partial u}{\partial x} \delta u \right|_0^L \right) \, dt
\end{align*}
$$

所以方程为

$$m\left( x \right)\frac{{{\partial ^2}u}}{{\partial {t^2}}} - \frac{\partial }{{\partial x}}\left( {EA\left( x \right)\frac{{\partial u}}{{\partial x}}} \right) = f\left( {x,t} \right)$$

边界条件

$${\left. {\left( {EA\left( x \right)\frac{{\partial u}}{{\partial x}} + ku} \right)} \right|_{x = 0}} = 0,\;\;{\left. {EA\left( x \right)\frac{{\partial u}}{{\partial x}}} \right|_{x = L}} = 0$$

## 2.2

令$u\left( {x,t} \right) = U\left( x \right){e^{i\omega t}}$, 代入

$$- m\left( x \right){\omega ^2}U\left( x \right){e^{i\omega t}} - \frac{\partial }{{\partial x}}\left( {EA\left( x \right)\frac{{\partial U\left( x \right)}}{{\partial x}}} \right){e^{i\omega t}} = 0$$
